Police said the car the man was driving may have been stolen as is often the case in smash-and-grab burglaries

Louetta Discount Liquor said the man made off with about $600 worth of alcohol during the burglary

The car be seen smashing through the front of the store in a surveillance video.

After he was in, the man  got out and collected cases of booze to take to his car.

He was unable to carry everything he collected and dropped a number of cases on the ground

The way he looked moving around in the store indicates he might have been intoxicated.

Louetta Discount Liquor said the man made off with about $600 worth of alcohol, according to a police reported obtained by Daily Mail Online. 

The man got away with three cases, including boxes of Smirnoff and Jack Daniels. 

